holster the other one first.

254
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:27,386
It's chilly out here.

255
00:20:31,297 --> 00:20:32,822
How did you find this place?

256
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:35,830
I know all the kinds of things.

257
00:20:37,203 --> 00:20:38,967
Your past, for instance.

258
00:20:41,006 --> 00:20:44,374
I know about poor
Isabella and that scar.

259
00:20:44,543 --> 00:20:47,638
<i>A slightly pat backstory if you
ask me, but that's hardly your fault.</i>

260
00:20:48,514 --> 00:20:49,982
I also know your future.

261
00:20:52,485 --> 00:20:54,010
You have none.

262
00:20:55,354 --> 00:20:56,549
Is that a threat?

263
00:20:57,356 --> 00:20:58,517
The start of a proposition,

264
00:20:59,558 --> 00:21:02,153
which you'll need after all.

265
00:21:02,862 --> 00:21:05,661
Your men are about to kill each
other over the safe you stole.

266
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:12,163
Tenderloin draws first and so on,
until only you and Armistice are left.

267
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:16,397
She calls you a damn
fool and you kill each other.

268
00:21:17,409 --> 00:21:19,071
You have quite the imagination.

269
00:21:21,013 --> 00:21:22,072
No.

270
00:21:23,349 --> 00:21:24,715
It's the ending you were given.

271
00:21:26,185 --> 00:21:27,425
<i>You threatening me?</i>

272
00:21:28,053 --> 00:21:29,112
<i>Go to hell!</i>

273
00:21:29,588 --> 00:21:31,548
<i>Or maybe we should just
clear out the dead weight.</i>

274
00:21:31,624 --> 00:21:33,559
- Stand down.
- You shut the fuck up.

275
00:21:33,759 --> 00:21:35,319
If you're gonna draw,
you better shoot.

276
00:21:35,361 --> 00:21:36,505
- Wait!
- You shut the fuck up!

277
00:21:36,529 --> 00:21:37,588
Go to hell.

278
00:21:45,538 --> 00:21:47,063
You damn fool.

279
00:21:55,414 --> 00:21:57,849
Now, the proposition.

280
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:02,755
I want you to break into hell
with me and rob the gods blind.

281
00:22:04,256 --> 00:22:05,849
Why would I do
anything with you?

282
00:22:06,926 --> 00:22:08,189
Because of what's in that safe.

283
00:22:09,862 --> 00:22:12,331
I have the combination. May I?

284
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:17,501
I could simply change
you, make you follow me.

285
00:22:18,938 --> 00:22:19,962
But that's not my way.

286
00:22:27,146 --> 00:22:30,776
I want you to see exactly what
the gods have in store for you.

287
00:22:31,817 --> 00:22:33,183
Because when you do,

288
00:22:33,452 --> 00:22:36,047
you won't have the faintest
idea of what to do with yourself.

289
00:22:38,057 --> 00:22:39,150
And I do.

290
00:23:00,312 --> 00:23:01,405
It's empty.

291
00:23:01,647 --> 00:23:02,740
<i>It was always empty,</i>

292
00:23:03,515 --> 00:23:04,983
like everything in this world.

293
00:23:06,151 --> 00:23:07,881
I died with my eyes open,

294
00:23:08,087 --> 00:23:10,056
